    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Making fine adjustments to a view’s position"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use SwiftUI to adaptively lay out and position your views.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If you can’t achieve your design with composition alone, fine tune the layout with view modifiers.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Add an offset modifier to shift the rendered content of a view from its current position, or a position modifier to set an explicit position within its parent.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-a-view-layout",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create a view layout",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following example provides a view to illustrate how to position views, providing a rough layout of views composed within a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/ZStack",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The stack contains a quadrant with an overlaid circle image:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "struct Crosshairs: View { ... } // Draws crosshairs.",
            "",
            "struct Quadrant: View {",
            "    var body: some View {",
            "        ZStack {",
            "            Crosshairs()",
            "            Rectangle()",
            "                .stroke(Color.primary)",
            "            Image(systemName: \"circle\")",
            "        }",
            "        .frame(width: 160, height: 160)",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "Making-Fine-Adjustments-to-a-View-s-Position-1.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more detail on composing views with stacks, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Building-Layouts-with-Stack-Views",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Shift-the-location-of-a-views-content",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Shift the location of a view’s content",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Fine-tune the position of the circle within the quadrant by using an offset modifier to shift where the parent view places the circle.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "An offset modifier shifts the image from its default center position.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/View/offset(x:y:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " modifier uses the parameters of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "x",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "y",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to represent a relative location within the view’s coordinate space.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In SwiftUI, the view’s coordinate space uses ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "x",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to represent a horizontal direction and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "y",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to represent a vertical direction.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The value of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "x",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " starts at ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " at the leading edge of a view, and increases as the location moves toward the trailing edge of a view.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The value of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "y",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " starts at ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " at the top edge of a view, and increases as the location moves toward the bottom edge of a view.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Don’t assume the leading edge is always on the left, because it changes with the layout direction.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When the layout direction is set to right-to-left, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " horizontal value is on the right side of the view.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following diagram shows the coordinates in the left-to-right layout direction against a rectangle, with the origin at the top, leading corner:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "Making-Fine-Adjustments-to-a-View-s-Position-2.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following example shifts the circle ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "40",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " points from the center, up and toward the trailing edge:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "struct Quadrant: View {",
            "    var body: some View {",
            "        ZStack {",
            "            Crosshairs()",
            "            Rectangle()",
            "                .stroke(Color.primary)",
            "            Image(systemName: \"circle\")",
            "                .offset(x: 40.0, y: -40.0)",
            "        }",
            "        .frame(width: 160, height: 160)",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "Making-Fine-Adjustments-to-a-View-s-Position-3.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Position-view-content-explicitly",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Position view content explicitly",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To explicitly position elements within a view, use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/View/position(x:y:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " view modifier.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "A position modifier overrides where the parent view places its content. The modifier renders the view at a location offset from the origin of the parent view, unlike an offset modifier that shifts the view from the location chosen by the parent view.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The position modifier uses the same ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "x",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "y",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " coordinate system as the offset modifier, and similarly doesn’t influence the size of the view.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "In this example, the position of the circle is set halfway down on the right side of the quadrant with explicit values:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "struct Quadrant: View {",
            "    var body: some View {",
            "        ZStack {",
            "            Crosshairs()",
            "            Rectangle()",
            "                .stroke(Color.primary)",
            "            Image(systemName: \"circle\")",
            "                .position(x: 144, y: 80)",
            "        }",
            "        .frame(width: 160, height: 160)",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "Making-Fine-Adjustments-to-a-View-s-Position-4.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
